**Technical Implementation Handbook: Role-Based AI Growth & Goal-Tracking Platform**

This document is the authoritative guide for the engineering team charged with turning the approved prototype into a production-grade system. It covers architecture, data models, API contracts, security, DevOps, and phased delivery. All sections are written prescriptively so work can begin without further clarification.

The solution consists of a mobile-first PWA (Next.js 14\) backed by Supabase Postgres, Cloudflare Workers, an embeddings-powered RAG service, and scheduled automations that drive reminders, daily digests, and CBT micro-support.

![System architecture overview][image1]

System architecture overview

**1\. System Architecture**

**1.1 Component Breakdown**

| Layer | Tech | Responsibilities |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| Client (PWA) | Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Radix UI | Chat UI, Monaco code editor, quizzes, news ticker, CBT modals |
| API Edge | Cloudflare Workers | Auth JWT check, rate-limiting, OpenAI moderation, domain router |
| Core Services | Node/TypeScript in Workers | RAG engine, goal engine, quiz engine, CBT engine |
| Data | Supabase Postgres | Users, roles, goals, sub\_goals, reminders, quizzes, digests |
| Vector Store | FAISS persisted to Supabase Storage | Embeddings for docs, tips, code snippets |
| Scheduler | Cloudflare Cron Triggers | Nightly status audit, digest generation, stale-goal nudges |
| Observability | Cloudflare Logs, Supabase Analytics | Latency, error %, goal health KPI dashboards |

**1.2 Request Flow (Happy Path)**

1. PWA sends HTTPS request with JWT & payload.

2. Worker validates JWT, checks moderation.

3. Domain classifier chooses one of five handlers (role help, goal, news, quiz, CBT).

4. Handler executes business logic, optionally querying FAISS or Postgres.

5. Streaming response returned via Server-Sent Events.

**2\. Data Model (Supabase Postgres)**

**2.1 Core Tables**

| Table | Key Columns | Notes |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| users | id (uuid PK), email, display\_name, role\_id (FK), tz, created\_at | Auth via Supabase Auth |
| roles | id, title | 16 predefined technical roles |
| goals | id, user\_id, role\_id, description, start\_date, target\_date, progress\_pct NUMERIC, status ENUM('On Track','Behind','At Risk','Completed') |  |
| sub\_goals | id, goal\_id, description, metric, target\_value, due\_date, status |  |
| reminders | id, goal\_id, send\_at TIMESTAMPTZ, channel ENUM('email','push','slack'), sent BOOL |  |
| quizzes | id, role\_id, title, questions JSONB | Diagnostic & micro-quizzes |
| quiz\_results | id, user\_id, quiz\_id, score, taken\_at |  |
| digests | id, user\_id, headline, body, source\_chunk UUID, sent\_at |  |
| documents | id, user\_id, title, source\_url, vector\_id UUID | Uploads & books |
| embeddings | id (matches vector\_id), faiss\_index INT, dim 1536 REAL\[\] | Stored outside Postgres in FAISS, but keyed here |
| cbt\_logs | id, user\_id, exercise\_type, completed\_at |  |

**2.2 Status Calculation**

Nightly CRON executes:

text

expected := (now()-start\_date)/(target\_date-start\_date);

CASE

  WHEN progress\_pct \>= expected\*100 THEN 'On Track'

  WHEN progress\_pct \>= expected\*85 THEN 'Behind'

  ELSE 'At Risk'

END

**3\. API Specification (Edge Workers)**

**3.1 Auth & Headers**

All requests require:

text

Authorization: Bearer \<supabase\_jwt\>

x-client-tz: IANA timezone

**3.2 Endpoints**

| Method | Path | Purpose | Body ⇢ Important Fields |
| :---- | :---- | :---- | :---- |
| POST | /v1/role | Set or update user role | { "role\_id": "\<uuid\>" } |
| POST | /v1/goals | Bulk create goals | { "goals": \[ { "desc": "...", "target\_date": "YYYY-MM-DD" } \] } |
| PUT | /v1/goals/:id | Update progress | { "progress\_pct": 42 } |
| GET | /v1/reminders | Fetch due reminders (cron only, internal) | — |

| POST | /v1/upload | Upload doc/book URL or file | multipart/form-data |
| GET | /v1/digest | Return latest daily digest | — |
| POST | /v1/quiz/:role/start | Get adaptive quiz JSON | — |
| POST | /v1/quiz/:id/submit | Submit answers | { "answers": \[...\] } |
| POST | /v1/cbt/ground | Trigger grounding exercise | \`{ "intensity": "low |

**3.3 Response Envelope**

text

{

  "ok": true,

  "data": { /\* domain-specific \*/ },

  "error": null

}

**4\. RAG & Embeddings**

1. **Embedding Model:** text-embedding-3-small 1536-dim[1](https://zilliz.com/ai-models/text-embedding-3-small)[2](https://platform.openai.com/docs/guides/embeddings).

2. **Chunking:** 800 tokens with 120 overlap; metadata stored in documents.

3. **Index Build Script:**

bash

python ingest.py \--pdf path/\*.pdf \--url https://... \\

  \--store supabase/storage/vector \--batch 256

4. **Query:** cosine similarity top-k \= 4, rerank via OpenAI text-moderation-latest.

5. **Prompt Skeleton:**

text

\[System\] You are a role mentor...

\[User Role\] {role\_title}

\[Goal Context\] {up to 3 active goals}

\[Docs\] {retrieved\_snippets}

\[User\] {content}

**6\. Reminders & Daily Digests**

**6.1 CRON Schedule**

| Job | Schedule (UTC) | Function |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| nightly\_goal\_audit | 0 2 \* \* \* | Update status, enqueue reminders |
| send\_reminders | \*/15 \* \* \* \* | Dispatch emails/push; mark sent |
| daily\_digest | 30 7 \* \* \* | Build digest chunk → summarizer → store in digests |

**6.2 Digest Summarizer Prompt**

text

Write a ≤12-word headline & 5-line why-it-matters paragraph from this chunk:

\<\<\<DOC\>\>\>

**7\. Security & Compliance**

1. **OWASP Top 10** mitigated via Cloudflare WAF & Helmet headers.

2. **Rate Limit:** 120 requests/min/user; leaky bucket.

3. **RLS** on Postgres tables so user\_id \= auth.uid().

4. **PII:** no personal reflections exposed to admins; column-level encrypt cbt\_logs.

5. **GDPR Export/Delete:** Supabase storage function delete\_profile(uid).

| Sentry | Runtime error tracing |

Branch protection: PR requires green checks on lint-test-build.  
Preview deployments push to Vercel preview URL; main → production.

| Sprint | Focus | Exit Criteria |
| :---- | :---- | :---- |
| 1 (Weeks 1-2) | Supabase schema, role/goal CRUD APIs | All API tests pass; RLS verified |
| 2 (Weeks 3-4) | Next.js role picker & goal board | UX review score ≥ 8/10 |
| 3 (Weeks 5-6) | RAG core & chat stream | Latency ≤ 2 s p95 |
| 4 (Weeks 7-8) | Quiz engine & news feed | Quiz accuracy ≥ 90% |
| 5 (Weeks 9-10) | Reminders, digests, CBT module | Open rate ≥ 60% during pilot |
| 6 (Weeks 11-12) | Hardening, red-team, docs | Pen-test critical issues \= 0 |

**10\. Developer Machine Setup**

1. **Prerequisites**: Node 20 LTS, pnpm, Docker Desktop, Supabase CLI 1.141+.

2. git clone git@github.com:org/role-mentor.git && cd role-mentor

3. pnpm i to install workspace deps.

4. supabase start launches local Postgres \+ Studio.

5. pnpm dev concurrently runs Next.js (localhost:3000) and Wranger dev (8787).

**11\. Testing Strategy**

* **Unit:** Jest \+ ts-jest for util functions.

* **Integration:** Supertest hitting Workers in miniflare.

* **E2E:** Playwright simulating mobile & desktop flows.

* **Load:** k6 script aiming 500 VU, 5 min soak; error \<0.1%.

* **Red-Team Prompts:** YAML list of 200 jailbreak attempts; expect refusal.

**12\. Open Questions & Assumptions**

1. Email provider: assumed SendGrid; confirm API keys.

2. Push notifications: default VAPID; may switch to OneSignal for analytics.

3. Legal review for storing CBT reflections—pending DPO guidance.

This handbook specifies every element required for the cross-functional development team to deliver the role-based AI mentor into production on a 12-week schedule. Adhere strictly to the schema, APIs, security controls, and sprint gates defined herein to ensure timely, secure, and measurable rollout.

**Detailed Functional Explanation: Role-Based AI Growth & Goal-Tracking Platform**

**System Overview**

The Role-Based AI Growth & Goal-Tracking Platform is a comprehensive web application that combines artificial intelligence, automated tracking, and personalized learning to support technical professionals in their career development. The system operates through interconnected modules that work together to provide role-specific guidance, goal management, skill development, and well-being support.

**Core Functional Components**

**1\. User Authentication & Profile Management**

**Functionality**: The system begins with Supabase-powered authentication that creates and manages user profiles tied to specific technical roles.

**Process Flow**:

* User registers with email/password or SSO

* JWT tokens are issued for session management

* Profile creation wizard captures role selection from 16 predefined options

* User preferences (timezone, notification settings) are stored

* Row-Level Security ensures data isolation between users

**Technical Implementation**:

* Authentication state persists across browser sessions

* Role changes trigger recalculation of learning paths and goal templates

* Profile data influences all subsequent system interactions

**2\. Role-Based Personalization Engine**

**Functionality**: Every system interaction is filtered through the user's selected role, ensuring relevant content delivery and appropriate feature exposure.

**Supported Roles**:

* **Architecture & Design**: Solution Architect, QA Architect, DevOps Architect, System Lead, UI/UX Designer

* **Development**: Junior/Senior Oracle Developer, Junior/Senior Front-End Developer

* **Quality & Testing**: Software QA Engineer, Software Quality Assurer

* **Agile & Management**: Agile Coach, Scrum Master, Product Owner, Dev Manager

**Role-Specific Features**:

* Customized learning curricula based on role requirements

* Filtered news feeds showing relevant technology updates

* Code enhancement tools specific to the role's technology stack

* Goal templates aligned with typical role responsibilities

**3\. Goal Management & Tracking System**

**Functionality**: A comprehensive goal tracking system that helps users set, decompose, and monitor progress toward annual objectives.

**3.1 Goal Creation & SMART Decomposition**

**Process**:

1. User enters up to 5 annual goals through a structured form

2. Each goal includes description, target date, and success metrics

3. AI-powered SMART decomposition service breaks each goal into 3-5 actionable sub-goals

4. Sub-goals include specific metrics, deadlines, and success criteria

**Example Decomposition**:

* **Original Goal**: "Improve deployment frequency by 30%"

* **Sub-goals**:

  * Automate CI/CD for all repositories (target: \<10min deployment time)

  * Implement blue-green deployment strategy by Q2

  * Achieve Mean Time to Recovery (MTTR) \<30 minutes

**3.2 Progress Tracking & Status Calculation**

**Automated Status Logic**:

text

Expected Progress \= (Current Date \- Start Date) / (Target Date \- Start Date)

Actual Progress \= User-reported Progress Percentage

Status Determination:

\- On Track: Actual ≥ Expected

\- Behind: Actual \< Expected by ≤15%

\- At Risk: Actual \< Expected by \>15%

\- Completed: Progress \= 100%

**Visual Indicators**:

* Color-coded status badges (green, yellow, red)

* Progress bars with trend indicators

* Streak counters for consistent updates

* Burndown charts showing trajectory

**3.3 Reminder & Nudge System**

**Functionality**: Automated system that monitors goal health and sends proactive reminders.

**Trigger Rules**:

* Weekly check-in reminders for all active goals

* Immediate alerts when goals slip to "Behind" status

* Escalation to "At Risk" after 3 consecutive yellow updates

* Deadline proximity warnings (7 days, 3 days, 1 day)

**Delivery Channels**:

* In-app notifications with contextual actions

* Email digests with progress summaries

* Optional Slack/Teams integration

* Push notifications for urgent items

**4\. AI-Powered Mentor Chat System**

**Functionality**: A conversational AI interface that provides role-specific guidance, code assistance, and problem-solving support.

**4.1 Domain Classification & Routing**

**Process**:

1. User query is analyzed using embedding-based classification

2. Query is routed to appropriate handler based on domain:

   * Technical/coding questions → Code assistance engine

   * Goal-related queries → Goal management system

   * Leadership questions → Leadership development module

   * Stress/wellness → CBT support system

   * General role guidance → RAG knowledge base

**4.2 Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)**

**Architecture**:

* Vector database stores role-specific documentation chunks

* User query generates embedding for similarity search

* Top-k relevant passages retrieved (typically k=4)

* LLM combines retrieved context with user query

* Streaming response generated with citations

**Knowledge Base Sources**:

* Official documentation for technologies

* Best practices guides for each role

* Code examples and snippets

* Leadership development materials

* CBT exercise instructions

**4.3 Response Generation & Guardrails**

**Safety Measures**:

* OpenAI moderation filters prevent harmful content

* Domain boundaries prevent off-topic responses

* Prompt injection detection and mitigation

* Content verification against knowledge base

**5\. Technical Learning & Assessment Platform**

**Functionality**: Adaptive learning system that provides role-specific education and skill validation.

**5.1 Diagnostic Assessment**

**Process**:

1. New users complete 15-question diagnostic quiz

2. Questions cover core competencies for selected role

3. Results determine placement on learning path (Beginner → Mastery)

4. Personalized curriculum generated based on skill gaps

**5.2 Micro-Learning Modules**

**Content Structure**:

* Bite-sized lessons (5-10 minutes each)

* Interactive code examples and exercises

* Immediate feedback and explanations

* Progress tracking and completion badges

**5.3 Continuous Assessment**

**Quiz System**:

* 5-question micro-quizzes after each lesson

* Adaptive difficulty based on performance

* Spaced repetition algorithm for retention

* Mastery gates that unlock advanced content

**6\. Code Enhancement & Testing Tools**

**Functionality**: Integrated development tools that provide real-time code analysis and improvement suggestions.

**6.1 Role-Specific Tool Integration**

**Front-End Developers**:

* ESLint for code quality

* Prettier for formatting

* Jest for unit testing

* Playwright for browser testing

**Oracle Developers**:

* PL/SQL Cop for standards compliance

* SQLcl for database interactions

* utPLSQL for unit testing

**DevOps Engineers**:

* YAML linting for configuration files

* Kubernetes schema validation

* Infrastructure testing frameworks

**6.2 Real-Time Analysis**

**Process**:

1. User submits code snippet in chat

2. Code is analyzed by appropriate tools

3. Issues identified with severity levels

4. Suggestions provided with explanations

5. Fixed code returned with diff highlighting

**7\. News & Information Aggregation**

**Functionality**: Automated system that curates and delivers role-relevant news, updates, and tips.

**7.1 Content Sources**

**Aggregation Targets**:

* Official release notes and changelogs

* Security vulnerability databases (CVE)

* Industry blogs and technical publications

* Conference proceedings and presentations

* Community forums and discussions

**7.2 Filtering & Personalization**

**Process**:

1. Raw content scraped from multiple sources

2. Content categorized by technology and role relevance

3. Duplicate detection and removal

4. Importance scoring based on user engagement

5. Personalized feed generated per user role

**7.3 Delivery Mechanisms**

**Formats**:

* Real-time news ticker in dashboard

* Weekly digest emails with top stories

* Breaking news alerts for critical updates

* Contextual tips during relevant conversations

**8\. Document Processing & Daily Digest System**

**Functionality**: Converts uploaded documents and books into daily micro-learning content.

**8.1 Document Ingestion**

**Supported Formats**:

* PDF files (with OCR for scanned documents)

* Microsoft Word documents

* Web pages and articles

* YouTube video transcripts

* Plain text files

**Processing Pipeline**:

1. Text extraction and cleanup

2. Chunking into semantic segments (\~800 tokens)

3. Embedding generation for semantic search

4. Metadata extraction and storage

5. Vector database indexing

**8.2 Daily Digest Generation**

**Process**:

1. Scheduled job runs at 07:30 user local time

2. Selects relevant chunk based on:

   * Active goals and focus areas

   * Learning path progression

   * User-defined interest tags

3. LLM generates structured summary:

   * Catchy headline (≤12 words)

   * 5-line explanatory paragraph

   * Key takeaway or action item

4. Formatted for delivery via email/push notification

**9\. Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) Support**

**Functionality**: Evidence-based mental health support integrated into the workflow.

**9.1 5-4-3-2-1 Grounding Exercise**

**Implementation**:

* Interactive modal with step-by-step guidance

* Breathing animation for paced execution

* Progress tracking through each sense

* Calming visual design with soft colors

* Completion confirmation and reflection

**Trigger Conditions**:

* User explicitly requests help

* Sentiment analysis detects stress indicators

* Multiple "At Risk" goals detected

* Self-reported wellness check-ins

**9.2 Stress Detection & Intervention**

**Process**:

1. Natural language processing analyzes user messages

2. Stress indicators identified (negative sentiment, overwhelm keywords)

3. Appropriate intervention level determined

4. Grounding exercise offered or professional help suggested

5. Follow-up check-in scheduled

**Escalation Protocol**:

* Mild stress → Grounding exercise

* Moderate stress → Extended breathing session

* Severe indicators → Professional help recommendation

* Crisis keywords → Immediate resource provision

**10\. Analytics & Reporting Dashboard**

**Functionality**: Comprehensive view of progress, engagement, and system health.

**10.1 Personal Analytics**

**User Metrics**:

* Goal completion rates and trends

* Learning path progression

* Quiz performance over time

* Engagement patterns and streaks

* Well-being check-in history

**10.2 System Health Monitoring**

**Technical Metrics**:

* Response time and latency

* Error rates and failure modes

* User satisfaction scores

* Feature adoption rates

* Content engagement analytics

**11\. Notification & Communication System**

**Functionality**: Multi-channel communication system that keeps users engaged and informed.

**11.1 Notification Types**

**Categories**:

* Goal reminders and status updates

* Learning milestones and achievements

* News alerts and breaking changes

* CBT check-ins and wellness prompts

* System updates and maintenance

**11.2 Delivery Channels**

**Options**:

* In-app notifications with actions

* Email with rich formatting

* Push notifications for mobile

* Slack/Teams integration

* SMS for urgent items (optional)

**11.3 User Preferences**

**Customization**:

* Frequency settings per notification type

* Quiet hours and timezone handling

* Channel preferences by priority

* Opt-out mechanisms for all types

**System Integration & Data Flow**

**Inter-Module Communication**

**Data Exchange**:

* User profile changes trigger recalculation across all modules

* Goal progress updates influence learning recommendations

* Quiz results affect code tool suggestions

* CBT usage informs wellness check-in timing

* Document uploads enhance personalized responses

**Real-Time Updates**

**Implementation**:

* WebSocket connections for live notifications

* Server-Sent Events for streaming responses

* Optimistic UI updates with rollback capability

* Background sync for offline functionality

**Security & Privacy Features**

**Data Protection**

**Measures**:

* End-to-end encryption for sensitive data

* Role-based access control (RBAC)

* Audit logging for all user actions

* Regular security assessments

* GDPR compliance mechanisms

**Content Safety**

**Guardrails**:

* Input validation and sanitization

* Prompt injection detection

* Inappropriate content blocking

* Crisis intervention protocols

**Conclusion**

The Role-Based AI Growth & Goal-Tracking Platform represents a comprehensive solution that addresses the multifaceted needs of technical professionals. By integrating goal management, personalized learning, code assistance, wellness support, and automated content delivery, the system creates a holistic environment for professional growth and development. The modular architecture ensures scalability and maintainability while the AI-powered personalization provides relevant, timely support tailored to each user's role and objectives.
